{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure boundary is model output quality: whether a real AI extractor actually finds all required terms in realistic legal text. Mocked/model-stubbed tests can validate schema handling but can hide missed extractions and phrasing sensitivity.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a curated set of real contract snippets with gold annotations for parties, dates, obligations, and penalties; assert recall/precision thresholds and verify repeated runs stay within an acceptable variance band.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on semantic judgment by the real model under policy context, especially for indirect/euphemistic phrasing. Deterministic mocks would likely pass while missing real false negatives/false positives.","test_description":"Evaluate the real risk-assessor model against a labeled corpus of direct and euphemistic risk examples for the target policy; assert detection-rate and false-positive limits, with multiple runs to observe model-output variability.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior is about substantive regulatory determination quality, not just wiring. The real model’s interpretation of legal language and jurisdictional rules is the core failure mode; mocks can hide classification errors.","test_description":"Run the real compliance checker on jurisdiction-specific contracts with expert-labeled pass/fail outcomes and requirement-level annotations; assert decision accuracy and critical-requirement miss rate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says \"standard\" but risk assessor says \"high risk\"), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure is at a module boundary: merge logic consuming outputs from multiple reviewer modules and preserving provenance. A pure unit test of merge internals may miss contract/schema mismatches between reviewer outputs and merger expectations.","test_description":"Wire real reviewer-output serializers/parsers (or production-format fixtures) into the merge module and assert that conflicting assessments for the same clause are both retained with correct reviewer attribution and no overwrite.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This requires multiple agentic steps in one end-to-end run (three AI reviewers) plus orchestration/merge guarantees. Real failures can emerge from parallel dispatch, partial returns, and cross-step aggregation, which lower-level isolated tests can miss.","test_description":"Execute the production pipeline on real contracts using all three real reviewers in parallel, then validate the final unified report contains each reviewer’s findings (including conflicts) with no dropped outputs across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
